President Biden delivered a speech at the Port of Baltimore, highlighting the importance of addressing supply chain disruptions and improving the country's infrastructure. He emphasized the need to stabilize the supply chain to lower prices and ensure that stores are fully stocked. The President discussed the challenges caused by the COVID-19 pandemic, which has led to disruptions in global supply chains. He outlined steps taken to address these issues, including working with major retailers and freight movers to improve the flow of goods. President Biden also highlighted the importance of investing in infrastructure, particularly in ports, to support economic growth and create jobs. He emphasized the need for a long-term view in building resilience and reducing reliance on foreign suppliers. The President also mentioned the passage of the Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill, which he believes will make significant progress in improving the country's infrastructure and addressing supply chain challenges.